HEADWORD: Shetland pony
<hw>Shet"land po"ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>One of a small, hardy breed
of horses, with long mane and tail, which originated in the Shetland
Islands; a sheltie.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

